# choose-voice — set or browse the TTS voice for Listen-Claude

Listen-Claude's read-aloud uses one of four engines: **edge** (free Microsoft neural, default), **system** (OS built-in), **piper** (local offline), **elevenlabs** (paid cloud). This skill helps the user pick a voice and writes the choice to `.env` so it takes effect on the next response.

## How to interpret the user's request

| User intent | Action |
|---|---|
| "list edge voices" / "Chinese voices" | Run `edge-tts --list-voices` (filter `zh` or `en`). |
| "list system voices" / "macOS voices" / "SAPI voices" | List built-in OS voices (see below). |
| "list piper voices" | List `.onnx` files under PIPER_VOICES_DIR. Direct user to https://rhasspy.github.io/piper-samples/ for downloads. |
| "download piper voice <name>" / "install piper voice <name>" | Run `install-piper-voice.{ps1,sh} <name>` to fetch from HuggingFace into PIPER_VOICES_DIR. |
| "browse ElevenLabs" | Tell user to open https://elevenlabs.io/app/voice-library, audition, and copy a voice_id. |
| "list my ElevenLabs voices" | Call ElevenLabs API (`/v1/voices`). Requires `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` in `.env`. |
| "use voice <id>" / "switch to <id>" | Run `set-voice.{ps1,sh}`. Auto-detect engine from format. |
| "what voice am I using" / "current voice" | Read TTS_VOICE and TTS_ENGINE from `__REPO_DIR__/.env`. |

## Engine auto-detection from voice ID format

When the user says "use voice X" without specifying the engine, infer it:

| Pattern | Engine |
|---|---|
| Matches `^(zh|en|ja|...)-[A-Z]{2}-[A-Za-z]+Neural$` (e.g. `zh-TW-HsiaoChenNeural`) | edge |
| Ends in `.onnx` or matches `^(zh_CN|en_US)-` (e.g. `zh_CN-huayan-medium`) | piper |
| 20-char alphanumeric ID (e.g. `21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM`) | elevenlabs |
| Anything else (display name like `Mei-Jia`, `Microsoft Yating Desktop`) | system |

## Listing voices

### Edge TTS (recommended free)
```bash
.venv/bin/edge-tts --list-voices | grep zh   # or en, ja, etc.
```
Popular Chinese voices: `zh-TW-HsiaoChenNeural` (TW 女), `zh-TW-YunJheNeural` (TW 男), `zh-CN-XiaoxiaoNeural` (CN 女), `zh-CN-YunyangNeural` (CN 男).

### System (macOS)
```
say -v '?' | grep -E 'zh|en'
```

### System (Windows)
```
powershell "Add-Type -AssemblyName System.Speech; (New-Object System.Speech.Synthesis.SpeechSynthesizer).GetInstalledVoices().VoiceInfo | Select Name,Culture"
```

### ElevenLabs (user's saved)
```bash
curl -s -H "xi-api-key: $ELEVENLABS_API_KEY" https://api.elevenlabs.io/v1/voices | jq '.voices[] | {voice_id, name}'
```

### ElevenLabs (community library)
Open https://elevenlabs.io/app/voice-library in a browser — has live preview the API doesn't match.

## Setting the voice

**Windows:**
```
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File "__REPO_DIR__\scripts\set-voice.ps1" -VoiceId <id> [-Engine <engine>]
```

**macOS / Linux:**
```
bash "__REPO_DIR__/scripts/set-voice.sh" <id> [<engine>]
```

`<engine>` is `edge`, `system`, `piper`, or `elevenlabs`. Omit if the engine is already configured correctly.

After setting, echo back the new `TTS_ENGINE` and `TTS_VOICE` values (the script prints them). No restart needed — the next Claude response will use the new voice.
